Feature: Canonical ".claude/settings.json" "SessionStart" keeps "bd prime" alongside "shop-msg prime" for both shop types

  Supersedes the "sole inner-hook command" property of scenario 75 (features/templates/75-canonical-lead-claude-settings-json-ships-with-bd-prime-as-sole-sessionstart-hook.gherkin) and scenario 96 (features/templates/96-canonical-bc-claude-settings-json-ships-with-bd-prime-as-sole-sessionstart-hook.gherkin). This scenario pins that "bd prime" is RETAINED (not removed) when "shop-msg prime" is added — the two hooks compose on SessionStart, each doing distinct orientation work ("bd prime" = beads workflow context; "shop-msg prime" = messaging DSN reachability + pending count). Both shop types carry both hooks; the BC primer in this repository already documents the BC-side composition explicitly ("Run 'shop-msg prime --bc <name>' ... Run 'bd prime' ..."), and PDR-009 brings the lead canonical into the same shape.

  @scenario_hash:7954bf8c04b829b4
  Scenario Outline: the canonical ".claude/settings.json" for "<shop_type>" has exactly one inner-hook "command" entry equal to "bd prime" AND exactly one inner-hook "command" entry equal to "shop-msg prime" under "hooks.SessionStart"
    When I ask the "shop-templates" package for the canonical ".claude/settings.json" template for shop type "<shop_type>" through its public template-access surface
    And the returned body is parsed as JSON
    Then exactly one inner-hook entry under "hooks.SessionStart" has a "command" string equal to the literal value "bd prime"
    And exactly one inner-hook entry under "hooks.SessionStart" has a "command" string equal to the literal value "shop-msg prime"
    And those two inner-hook entries are distinct entries (the canonical does not pack both commands into a single "command" string via shell composition such as "bd prime && shop-msg prime")

    Examples:
      | shop_type |
      | bc        |
      | lead      |
